The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 2 YEARS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 1 YEAR and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 1 YEAR, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 1 DAY time served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 3 YEARS with the following conditions for PROBATION and EXTENDED SUPERVISION:

Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

-Restitution set at $300.00 payable to Michael T., $165.00 to Jamie S.. joint/several with co-defendants Darius Kinney, Darrin Kinney, Tristain Louis-Saffold, to be collected during term of probation. -No association with drug users, drug dealers and drug houses or otherwise engage in drug dealing
-Cooperate with agent

Amended Information filed.  Defense counsel acknowledged receipt of a copy of the Information, waived its reading.

Defendant prepared to enter guilty plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AMENDED COUNT 2:  The defendant was advised of her constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and, Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for to sustain the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  Filed, Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.  Adjourned date before Branch 21 selected with the parties.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for October 15, 2015 at 08:30 am.
